      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The photograph shows a part of the cinema’s front wall announcing the screening of the feature ‘Wall Street’.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Cinema ‘Corso’ was founded in the interwar period. The announced feature ‘Wall Street’ was directed by Roy William Neill and released in 1929. The cinema, which was renamed ‘Victoria’ in communist time, is located in Bulevardul Regina Elisabeta 27.</ab>
